标  题: Re: 从GPL协议出发驳斥SYSOP的谎言
蛋蛋们跟你解释真是太没面子了。
你只是用个客户端访问这个地方，
你是客户端程序 -- CTerm, FTerm等等的用户。
蛋蛋们又没提供任何程序给你，
你是没有理由要求他们公开任何代码的。
所谓“程序的用户”是直接使用程序的人们，
蛋蛋们是使用并修改原来站务所写程序来开办服务的用户，
明白了么？
唉，很久没来，没想到还在这么没品的问题上吵吵。
     标  题: 从GPL协议出发驳斥SYSOP的谎言
     
     http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#GPLRequireSourcePostedPublic
     里面写的很清楚:
     Does the GPL require that source code of modified versions be posted to the public? 
     The GPL does not require you to release your modified version. You are free to make modifications and use them privately, without ever releasing them. This applies to organizations (including companies), too; an organization can make a modified version and use it internally without ever releasing it outside the organization. 
     But if you release the modified version to the public in some way, the GPL requires you to make the modified source code available to the program\'s users, under the GPL.
     
     Thus, the GPL gives permission to release the modified program in certain ways, and not in other ways; but the decision of whether to release it is up to you. 
     
     注意，GPL协议规定只有在软件被应用在一个特定组织范围之类的时候，才不需要按照GPL协议公布源代码。蛋蛋们站出来告诉我，放在互联网上让任何人都可以访问，算不算releasing it outside the organization？
     
     --
